cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and neural machine translation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to composing representations learned by different components in neural machine translation, which involves modeling strong interactions among neurons. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. Additionally, the paper leverages bilinear pooling to model pairwise multiplicative interactions among individual neurons, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper includes experiments on WMT14 English-German and English-French translation tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category.
